## Plan Summary

**Only one file needs to change: `src/routes.ts`**

The test suite already exists and fully defines the contract. Here's exactly what to do:

### The change

Replace the `GET /users` handler body in `src/routes.ts`:

```ts
// BEFORE
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  res.json(users);
});

// AFTER
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1);
  const limit = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10);

  const total      = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const data       = users.slice((page - 1) * limit, page * limit);

  res.json({
    data,
    pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages },
  });
});
```

### Why this works for every test case

| Test | Query | Result |
|------|-------|--------|
| Default | `GET /users` | page=1, limit=10 → 10 items, totalPages=2 |
| Second page | `?page=2&limit=10` | items 11–15 → 5 items |
| Custom limit | `?limit=5` | 5 items, totalPages=3 |
| Out-of-range | `?page=100` | `slice(990, 1000)` on 15-item array → `[]`, status 200 |

- **Out-of-range pages** are handled for free — `Array.slice` returns `[]` for offsets beyond array length, no special-casing needed.
- `Math.max(1, ...)` guards against zero/negative inputs.
- No other files (`data.ts`, `types.ts`, `app.ts`, tests) need modification.
